1.2: This subclass of HTMLElement is used when only a HTMLElement is possible and not any of its subclasses. Normally, a type can refer to an instance of itself or an instance of any subtype. More concretely, if HTMLElement is used then the compiler must assume that it might still be e.g. HTMLScriptElement. With this, the type check knows that it couldn't be any special element.

This subclass of HTMLElement is used when only a HTMLElement is possible and not any of its subclasses. Normally, a type can refer to an instance of itself or an instance of any subtype. More concretely, if HTMLElement is used then the compiler must assume that it might still be e.g. HTMLScriptElement. With this, the type check knows that it couldn't be any special element.
